# ISSUE-11-Implement-UI-For-Virtual-Pantry-View-Pantry-List

**Issue Type:** Documentation

## Objective:

Key Requirements:

- Implement the UI screen for viewing pantry items.
• Build list view component.
• Ensure items render cleanly in a scrollable list.
• Add placeholder state for when pantry is empty.
• Style according to design mockups

## Description:

- This branch is used to create the UI for the pantry screen where users can view their pantry items. 
The screen includes a list view component that displays pantry items in a scrollable format. If the pantry is empty, 
a placeholder state is shown to inform users. The UI is styled according to the provided design mockups to ensure a consistent and visually appealing user experience.
-As well as the home page where users can see their pantries and add new ones

## Learnings:

- Learned how to use React Native components to create a scrollable list view.

## What's next:

- Is to Implement View Pantry List Functionality. This includes fetching pantry items from the 
backend and displaying them in the list view.

